Sentencas: Redox cycling of Ni-based anode induces cell degradation which limits the cell's lifetime during solid oxide fuel cell operation.
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes

Sentencas: In the present study, the redox testing of electrolyte-supported cells has been investigated with TiO2-added NiO-YSZ anode matrix.
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes

Sentencas: Button cells were fabricated by die-pressing YSZ powder as electrolyte, and onto which NiO-YSZ or NiO-TiO2-YSZ anode and LSM-YSZ composite cathode were painted.
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance and stability have been evaluated by measuring current-voltage characteristics followed by impedance spectroscopy after each redox cycling.
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes

Sentencas: Anode matrices before and after cell operation have been characterized by X-ray diffraction (XRD), elemental dispersive X-ray (EDX), and scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes

Sentencas: During cell operation the peak power density decreases from 111 mW cm(-2) (239 mA cm(-2)) to 84 mW cm(-2) (188 mA cm(-2)) between 23 and 128 h with five redox cycles for cell having NiO-YSZ (40:60) anode.
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes

Sentencas: But for cell with NiO-TiO2-YSZ (30:10:60), the anode peak power density was constant and stable around 85 mW cm(-2) (194 mA cm(-2)) throughout the cell run of 130 h and five redox cycles.
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes

Sentencas: No loss in the open circuit voltage was observed.
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes

Sentencas: SEM and XRD studies of NiO-TiO2-YSZ (30:10:60) anodes revealed formation of ZrTiO4, which may be responsible for inhibition of Ni coarsening leading to stable cell performance.
Titulo: Performance studies of electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni-YSZ and Ni-TiO2-YSZ as anodes
